‘He told us, “For every person that escapes, I will shoot two”. That was when I lost hope,’ Mikhael recounted tearfully.

‘That’s when I asked him if I could call my kids and if I could speak to them.’

‘I actually wanted to hear their voices for the last time.’

Ms Mikhael is a 43-year-old mother of three from Glenwood in Sydney’s northwest.

She was desperate to tell her children that she loved them, believing Monis would soon shoot her dead.

‘I told them that I loved them very much and I needed them to remember that,’ Mikhael said.

‘My eldest son kept telling me ‘Mum, stop it, everything’s going to be okay’ and I kept telling him ‘I know, I know but just remember that I love you, I love you so much’ and then I had to hang up.' 

