Hostage Selina Win Pe has revealed the horrifying moment crazed gunman Man Haron Monis told her she had just 15 minutes to live.

Monis turned to Ms Win Pe during the height of the siege in the Lindt Cafe at Martin Place, where he took 18 people hostage on December 15, and forced her to beg for her life. 

'I said please don’t shoot me, please don’t shoot me,' she told 60 Minutes in an upcoming special to air on Channel Nine.

'I only have my mum, please don’t shoot me. He looked me straight in the eyes and said "you have 15 minutes"'.  

